                                                                    "value": "For specific visa types, some institutions may also need to be certified by specific governing bodies. For example, students with a J-1 visa can only enroll in programs approved by the Department of State Bureau of Educational and Cultural Affairs. For F-1 students, programs must be certified by the Student and Exchange Visitor Program (SEVP). This information is listed in your SEVIS record and is part of the documentation you need to transfer. ",
